              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "1",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "2SWTPSI"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " PSI multi-user accelerator facility,",
                " 590 MeV PSI ring cyclotron, power > 1.2MW."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "2",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CHOPS"
                ],
                "institute": "2FR ILL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Very slow neutrons from turbine at ILL",
                "pass through a chopper operating at duty cycle of 5.5%",
                "and frequency of 0.81 Hz.",
                "Experiment was designed and built at PSI.",
                "The data acquisition took place at ILL."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "1",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "SPALL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "Spallation target made of lead-filled Zircaloy",
                "tubes. Proton beam is pulsed with the duty cycle 1%,",
                "for 8 sec every 800 sec. Spallation neutron are",
                "thermalyzed in 3.5 m**3 heavy water (purity 99.75%).",
                "In the center of heavy water volume , the cold UCN",
                "converter at 5 K temperature is installed, consisted of",
                "a vessel filled with solid deuterium(purity 99.95%)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "1",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Thermalyzed spallation neutrons can be downscattered",
                "into ultracold and very cold neutron range",
                " (E-kin <500 neV) by phonon excitation. Neutrons leave",
                "the cold converter,pass through the thin material of",
                "the top lid, then slowed down by gravity from 5 - 9 m/s",
                "to 0 - 7 m/s, and become storable in the about 2 m**3",
                "UCN storage volume of 2.5 m high."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "2",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Very slow neutrons of 3-20 m/sec."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "2",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRN",
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Transmission of very slow neutrons (3-20 m/s)",
                "  was measured by time-of-flight method.",
                "Flight path 2.270 m. TOF spectra were measured with and",
                "without sample.TOF system was calibrated by recording",
                "TOF spectra of foil at two different flight paths."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Samples of different material and thickness(0.01-1 mm).",
                "Sample holder at 2.220 m distance from the chopper.",
                "Surface roughness of the samples was not quantified."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron detector was installed closely behind sample,",
                " about 50 mm distance."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Experimental values for the total cross-sections were",
                "extracted from fits of transmission data with",
                "exponentials."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Spherically shaped samples (Zircaloy and AlMg3) were",
                "used to investigate UCN transmission through the",
                "dome-like structure. Transmission probability decreases",
                "with increasing dome height."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
